# Markdown Formatting Standards

## Heading Structure
- Use consistent heading hierarchy (# ## ### ####)
- Keep headings concise and descriptive
- Use sentence case for headings
- Include emoji indicators where appropriate (as shown in [it strategy starter.md](mdc:it strategy starter.md))

## Section Organization
- Follow the established template structure from [it strategy starter.md](mdc:it strategy starter.md)
- Use horizontal rules (---) to separate major sections
- Maintain consistent spacing between sections

## Content Formatting
- Use bullet points for lists and sub-items
- Bold (**text**) for emphasis on key terms and concepts
- Italics (*text*) for definitions or clarifications
- Code blocks (```) for technical specifications when needed

## Business Document Standards
- Write in professional business language
- Use active voice where possible
- Keep sentences clear and concise
- Include specific metrics and measurable outcomes
- Maintain consistent terminology throughout documents

## Template Compliance
- Preserve the question-answer-draft structure from the starter template
- Fill in "Your Answers" sections before generating draft content
- Keep placeholder comments until ready to replace with actual content
